recalls.Summary: Nissan North America, Inc. (Nissan) is recalling certain 2016-2018 Infiniti Q50 and 2017 Infiniti Q60 vehicles equipped with a 2.0L engine.  Incorrect Fuel Pump Control Module (FPCM) software may allow the fuel level in the main tank to be too low to supply fuel to the engine, causing the engine to stall while driving.
recalls.Consequence: An engine stall can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Nissan will notify owners, and Infiniti dealers will reprogram the Fuel Pump Control Module (FPCM) with corrected software, free of charge.  The recall began August 29, 2017.  Owners may contact Infiniti customer service at 1-800-662-6200.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

The evening of April 17th, 2022, I started experiencing an issue with my vehicle. My car started making a fluttering noise it sounded like someone was shuffling a deck of cards and the RPMs would get to 3 during acceleration then drop and I’d lose power. There were no warning lights present, no notification or indicators on my dash, no odors, and no smoke emitting from my car. I parked my car at home not knowing what the issue was or where the noise was coming from. The next morning, I called to schedule an appointment and I booked with Infiniti in Timonium. After scheduling my appointment, I went out to check my car and when I started it the noise was still there. It ran for a few seconds then my check engine light cut on. Looking to get a pre-diagnosis to have additional info about the condition of my car I take it to Autozone on liberty road to have codes pulled. The codes that came back were P0014 and P0024 both camshaft codes. However, there were still no other symptoms of odor or smoke just the fluttering noise and now my check engine light. On the way back home my car stalls at Liberty Road and Rolling Road and won’t cut back on. I contacted AAA and had it towed to Infiniti the same day. I was assigned to [XXX] as my service advisor. The car was at Infiniti in Timonium for close to a month when [XXX] reached out to notify me of the presence of sludge and metal shavings in my oil pan and my engine being seized.  He was adamant that it came from a lack of maintenance. I was using my third-party warranty and they requested that I send proof of maintenance. I submitted my maintenance invoices to Sean, and he forwarded them to my Warranty Company. I provided invoices for my last 3 oil changes. I wasn’t due for a fourth for another 6-700 miles. I bought my car at 35,796 miles and I’m currently at 70,042 (42 miles out of the power train warranty). I followed manufactures 10k guideline. The vehicle is available for inspection upon request.  INFORMATION Redacted PURSUANT TO THE FREEDOM OF INFORMATION ACT (FOIA), 5 U.S.C. 552(B)(6).

Initial fault was no cabin heat.  Service department determined coolant was low.  Coolant system passed pressure test.  Coolant was found to be leaking into cylinders past head gaskets.  After head gasket replacement, engine broke down on highway and car was towed to dealership.  Catastrophic overheat damage in lower end.  Engine long block was replaced to correct.  Multiple identical/similar occurrences reported on infinitiq60.org.  Failure is normally failed head gasket or porous engine block.  2017 models especially affected.  Infiniti consumer affairs completely unresponsive if vehicle is outside powertrain warranty.  Safety at risk due to potential engine failure and vehicle stoppage at any time.  No indications received at any time indicating failure.  Temp gauge never indicated spike or failure.  Only indication was lack of cabin heat, but coolant was basically empty.  The problem was reproduced by dealer after servicing coolant and seeing subsequent engine internal consumption of coolant.  Vehicle was inspected by Infiniti service department and MPP third-party warranty company.  All vehicle service records since purchase are available.

I recently have bought this car. I had heard an issue with the Serpentine belt/Tensioner and the belts where making a chirp during 1,500- 3,000 rpm.  I took it into the dealership 10 days after I bought it  while the vehicle was still under factory warranty and they said they inspected the belt system and could not replicate the issue. Later in the year I was able to get a video of the vehicle making the noise and called and scheduled another appointment. After I made the appointment I started researching online I came across I was not the only Consumer having issues with the Serpentine belt/Tensioner and Infiniti put out a Service Bulletin # ITB17-004 in regards to this issue. Looking at the bulletin I discovered that my vin fell in that spectrum of vin related to the service bulletin. I was able to get my car fixed the tensioner and serpentine belt got replaced with my extended warranty. Infiniti would not fix my car because it was past the time period on the powertrain warranty even though my my car only had 36,000 miles when I first discovered the issue. I understand the difference from a service bulletin and a recall. But I want to report this issue because there is obviously a quality issue with these serpentine belts and tensioner in specific to the 3.0  twin turbo engine that could cause a safety issues for consumers. I am advocating for other consumers and their safety because if this serpentine belt and tensioner where to fail while in motion making the car stall and over heat while on the road this could cause sever danger to patrons of the highway and could result in death. This service bulletin issue needs to be turned into a recall.

THE VEHICLE IS VERY NEW- ONLY 7000 MILES ON IT. I WAS DRIVING ON A MAJOR INTERSTATE AT APPROXIMATELY 60 MPH WHEN THE VEHICLE SUDDENLY SHUT DOWN. THE ENGINE JUST SHUT OFF AND NO POWER.  THE ENGINE SHUT DOWN WHILE WE WERE TRAVELLING ON A HIGHWAY!! THERE WERE CHILDREN IN THE CAR, AND LUCKILY I WAS ABLE TO PULL TO THE SHOULDER WITHOUT BEING STRUCK. NEEDLESS TO SAY IT WAS A VERY DANGEROUS SITUATION- WE COULD HAVE BEEN KILLED. THE CAR THEN WOULD NOT START. WE HAD 3/4 TANK OF FUEL. IT REQUIRED TO BE TOWED TO THE DEALER , PEPE INFINITI IN WHITE PLAINS, NY. THE DEALER HAS HAD THE VEHICLE OVER A WEEK AND HAS NOT BEEN ABLE TO DETERMINE WHAT HAPPENED. THEY STATE THAT THE FUEL WAS TESTED FOR CONTAMINANTS BUT CAME BACK CLEAN. NOW THEY WANT TO GIVE THE VEHICLE BACK SAYING THAT THEY DONT KNOW WHAT HAPPENED BUT "MAYBE" IT WAS THE FUEL. REALLY? THEY HAD FUEL TESTED AND IT WAS FINE. I THINK THEY AND THE MANUFACTURER ARE COVERING THIS UP TO AVOID WIDESPREAD PROBLEMS. HOW CAN THEY NOT DETERMINE THE PROBLEM? IF THIS HAPPENS AGAIN WE CAN POTENTIALLY BE KILLED!! WHAT ABOUT THE OTHER VEHICLES POUT THERE? WHAT IF IT HAPPENS TO THEM? SOMETHING NEEDS TO BE DONE- THIS NEEDS TO BE INVESTIGATED!!

THREE-MONTH-OLD 2017 INFINITI Q60 SUNROOF SPONTANEOUSLY EXPLODES. ON THE MORNING OF MAY 22, 2017 AROUND 6:30 AM, I WAS DRIVING TO WORK ON MY NORMAL ROUTE WEST ON I-10 GOING THE SPEED LIMIT AND NEAR THE SIEGEN LANE EXIT FIRST HEARD A SMALL POP LIKE SOMETHING HITTING THE WINDSHIELD BUT NO EVIDENCE COULD BE SEEN OF THIS OCCURRING. ABOUT 30 SECONDS TO A MINUTE LATER HEARD A LOUD EXPLOSION LIKE A TIRE BLOWOUT THEN A LOT OF ROAD NOISE AND WIND. I PULLED OVER AND STOPPED TO FIND OUT MY SUNROOF GLASS WAS MOSTLY GONE, BROKEN INTO SMALL FRAGMENTS AND A HOLE BLOWN THROUGH. THANKFULLY, MY SUNROOF WAS DOWN, SCREEN CLOSED, AND NO GLASS GOT INTO THE CAR.    I INITIALLY THOUGHT SOMETHING HAD HIT IT OR SOMEONE THROUGH SOMETHING. HOWEVER, THERE WAS NO ONE NEAR ME AT THE TIME AND I WAS IN THE MIDDLE LANE OF THE HIGHWAY, NOR WAS THERE ANY DEBRIS THAT HIT THE CAR OR ADDITIONAL DAMAGE. IN ADDITION, NOTHING VISIBLE IN THE SUNROOF.  FURTHERMORE, THE SUNROOF WAS DOWN AND CLOSED MAKING IMPACT BY DEBRIS VERY HARD. IT WAS RAINING SO I PULLED INTO THE NEAREST GAS STATION, WHICH WAS RACETRAC ON SIEGEN LANE AND REQUESTED A GARBAGE BAG TO COVER THE DAMAGE AND MITIGATE ANY FURTHER DAMAGE FROM THE WEATHER. I PROCEEDED TO CALL MY INSURANCE COMPANY TO MAKE A CLAIM AND REQUEST A TOW TO INFINITI OF BATON ROUGE FOR POTENTIAL REPAIRS. AFTER CONFIRMING A TOW, I BEGAN TO CALL AND GET QUOTES FOR THE REPAIRS.     ONCE AT WORK I STARTED TO TALK TO MY CO-WORKERS AND THEY RECOMMENDED THAT I GOOGLE EXPLODING INFINITI SUNROOFS BECAUSE THE OCCURRENCE WAS NOT SOMETHING NORMAL. I BEGAN TO RESEARCH AND FOUND THAT THIS WEIRD OCCURRENCE IS MORE COMMON THAN I THOUGHT. I FOUND VARIOUS OCCURRENCES ACROSS A WIDE VARIETY OF MANUFACTURES AND VEHICLES MODELS. I SUBMITTED A CLAIM TO INFINITI CONSUMER AFFAIRS AND I AM AWAITING A RESPONSE BY COB TOMORROW.

WHILE DRIVING ON AN INTERSTATE HIGHWAY AT 70 MPH, THE ENGINE TURNED OFF WITHOUT WARNING.  THE ECO-MODE LIGHTS CAME ON WITH "SYSTEM FAILURE" WARNING.  I WAS ABLE TO COAST INTO THE BREAKDOWN LANE.  THE CAR WOULD NOT RESTART RIGHT AWAY.  AFTER WORKING WITH THE TOW TRUCK DRIVER, WE WERE ABLE TO GET THE CAR STARTED AFTER ABOUT ONE HOUR.  I DID NOT FEEL SAFE DRIVING THE CAR SO IT WAS TOWED TO MY HOME.  THE NEXT MORNING, IT WAS TOWED TO THE DEALER FOR REPAIRS.  THEY CONTACTED INFINITI'S TECH LINE AND WAS TOLD THIS IS A KNOWN ISSUE AND THEY ARE WORKING ON A FIX.  TO AVOID THIS HAPPENING AGAIN, THEY RECOMMEND KEEPING THE GAS TANK ABOVE 50% FULL.  THEY DO NOT HAVE AN ETA FOR THE FIX.  I HAVE CONTACTED INFINITI CONSUMER AFFAIRS AND THEY COULD NOT TELL ME ANYTHING MORE.  I FEEL THE VEHICLE IS NOT SAFE TO DRIVE.  I HAVE ATTACHED THE REPAIR ORDER FROM INFINITI.

issues.title: VR30DDTT Engine Oil Consumption and Burning Issues
issues.description: The VR30DDTT twin-turbo engine experiences excessive oil consumption, often requiring oil top-offs between scheduled maintenance intervals. Some owners report burning oil smell and blue smoke from exhaust.
issues.fix_description: Engine rebuild or replacement may be required in severe cases. Short-term fixes include more frequent oil changes and monitoring.
issues.prevention: Use high-quality synthetic oil, change oil more frequently than recommended, avoid aggressive driving during break-in period

issues.title: Turbocharger Failure and Oil Starvation
issues.description: Premature turbocharger failure due to oil starvation, contamination, or manufacturing defects. Can result in complete engine damage if metal debris enters the engine.
issues.fix_description: Complete turbocharger replacement, engine inspection for debris, oil system cleaning
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, allow proper warm-up and cool-down periods, use recommended oil grade

issues.title: 7-Speed Automatic Transmission Jerking and Harsh Shifting
issues.description: The 7-speed automatic transmission exhibits harsh shifting, jerking during gear changes, and hesitation during acceleration, particularly in lower gears.
issues.fix_description: Transmission software updates, valve body replacement, or transmission rebuild in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes, avoid aggressive driving, allow transmission to warm up

issues.title: Power Steering Failure and Hard Steering
issues.description: Electric power steering system failures resulting in heavy steering, complete loss of power assist, and steering wheel vibration.
issues.fix_description: Power steering motor replacement, steering rack repair, or ECU replacement
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of power steering system, avoid extreme steering angles when parked

issues.title: Brake System Vibration and Premature Rotor Warping
issues.description: Front brake rotors warp prematurely causing steering wheel vibration during braking, particularly on Red Sport models with larger brake systems.
issues.fix_description: Rotor replacement or resurfacing, brake pad replacement, proper bedding procedure
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive braking, allow brakes to cool after spirited driving, proper brake bedding

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Black Screen
issues.description: The dual-screen infotainment system experiences random freezing, black screens, and failure to respond to inputs, affecting navigation and climate control.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, infotainment unit replacement, or hard reset procedures
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid extreme temperatures, proper shutdown procedures

issues.title: Carbon Buildup in Direct Injection Engine
issues.description: Direct injection engines accumulate carbon deposits on intake valves, causing rough idle, misfiring, and reduced performance over time.
issues.fix_description: Walnut blasting or chemical cleaning of intake valves, fuel system cleaning
issues.prevention: Use top-tier gasoline, occasional high-RPM driving, fuel system cleaners

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Failure
issues.description: A/C compressor failures result in no cooling, unusual noises from the compressor, and refrigerant leaks, particularly in warmer climates.
issues.fix_description: A/C compressor replacement, refrigerant system evacuation and recharge
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system maintenance, run A/C periodically during winter months

issues.title: Door Handle and Window Regulator Issues
issues.description: Interior and exterior door handles break or become loose, and window regulators fail causing windows to drop or operate slowly.
issues.fix_description: Door handle replacement, window regulator motor or mechanism replacement
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of handles and windows, regular lubrication of window tracks

issues.title: Fuel Pump High Pressure System Failures
issues.description: High-pressure fuel pump failures in the direct injection system cause starting issues, stalling, and loss of power, particularly under load.
issues.fix_description: High-pressure fuel pump replacement, fuel system pressure testing
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, replace fuel filter as recommended, avoid running on very low fuel

issues.title: Suspension Component Premature Wear
issues.description: Front suspension components including control arms, bushings, and struts show premature wear, particularly on Red Sport models with sport suspension.
issues.fix_description: Replacement of worn suspension components, alignment, balancing
issues.prevention: Avoid potholes and rough roads, regular alignment checks, proper tire pressure

editorial.tagline: Twin-turbo fury wrapped in Japanese luxury elegance
editorial.hero_blurb: The Q60 Red Sport 400 delivers 400 horsepower through a sophisticated twin-turbo V6, wrapped in stunning coupe bodywork. It's Infiniti's answer to the German sport coupe establishment, offering distinctive styling and genuine performance capability.
editorial.essence: This is Infiniti's most potent coupe, combining genuine twin-turbo performance with distinctive Japanese luxury design language. The Red Sport 400 stands apart from Germanic competitors with its flowing lines, premium interior, and characterful VR30 engine.
editorial.heritage: Born from Infiniti's G37 coupe lineage and the brand's performance ambitions, the Q60 represents the evolution of Nissan's luxury performance coupe DNA. It carries forward the spirit of the beloved G35/G37 while embracing modern turbocharging technology.
editorial.design_philosophy: Infiniti's designers pursued emotional, flowing lines over clinical precision, creating a coupe that emphasizes sensual curves and dramatic proportions. The goal was to stand apart from angular German competitors with distinctly Japanese aesthetic sensibilities.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not directly race-bred, the Q60 shares its VR30DDTT engine with Infiniti's Formula One involvement and draws from Nissan's extensive motorsport heritage, including GT-R development programs.
editorial.engine_character: The VR30DDTT feels eager and responsive, delivering smooth power delivery with minimal turbo lag. It's refined yet characterful, providing strong mid-range punch with a sophisticated, almost GT-like demeanor rather than raw aggression.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 7-speed automatic shifts smoothly in comfort mode but can feel sluggish in manual mode. Sport+ sharpens responses considerably, though it lacks the lightning-quick reflexes of dual-clutch systems.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The adaptive suspension provides a well-balanced compromise between comfort and sport, with Dynamic Digital Suspension offering meaningful adjustability. The chassis feels composed and planted, if not quite as sharp as its German rivals.
editorial.steering_feel: Direct-Adaptive Steering provides good on-center feel and reasonable feedback, though it lacks the pure mechanical connection enthusiasts crave. Weight builds progressively, but the system can feel slightly artificial at times.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive brakes with good pedal feel and adequate cooling for spirited driving. The system inspires confidence in both daily driving and more aggressive scenarios, though serious track use may require upgrades.
editorial.sound_signature: A sophisticated twin-turbo growl with active exhaust enhancement that adds theater without becoming obnoxious. The note is more refined than aggressive, with pleasant induction sounds under acceleration.
editorial.ideal_owner: Luxury coupe buyers who want something different from the German establishment, appreciate distinctive design, and desire genuine performance with everyday usability and comfort.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Hardcore track enthusiasts, manual transmission purists, or buyers prioritizing maximum performance per dollar over luxury appointments and unique styling.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for 2019+ models with updated infotainment and refined dynamics. The Red Sport 400 offers genuine performance alternative to German coupes with distinctive style, though it prioritizes luxury over razor-sharp dynamics.
cons: Not as sharp dynamically as German rivals
